---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const basePath = baseUrl.endsWith('/') ? baseUrl : `${baseUrl}/`;
---

<BaseLayout title="Portfolio | Robert Otieno | Enterprise Identity & Security Architect" description="Enterprise-scale identity, security & IT operations portfolio. Zero Trust architecture, privacy-engineered systems, automation-driven governance.">
	<section class="hero" style="margin-top: 0;">
		<div>
		<p class="eyebrow">Enterprise Identity, Security & IT Operations Architect</p>
		<h1>Robert Otieno</h1>
		<p class="lead">Zero Trust Identity, Privacy-Engineered Systems, Automation-Driven Enterprise Security</p>
		<p>I architect enterprise identity and security systems built on zero-trust principles, privacy-by-design, and intelligent automation. My approach blends deep IAM/governance expertise with modern cloud infrastructure and emerging digital identity standards.</p>
		<div class="cta-row">
			<a class="cta" href={`${basePath}projects/`}>Case Studies</a>
			<a class="cta" href={`${basePath}about/`}>Approach & Strategy</a>
		</div>
		</div>
		<div class="hero-art" aria-hidden="true">
			<svg viewBox="0 0 420 280" width="100%">
				<rect x="24" y="24" width="372" height="232" rx="10" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#cbd5e1" />
				<rect x="44" y="44" width="148" height="52" rx="8" fill="#f8faff" stroke="#1e3a8a" />
				<rect x="212" y="44" width="164" height="52" rx="8" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#cbd5e1" />
				<rect x="44" y="116" width="332" height="52" rx="8" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#cbd5e1" />
				<rect x="44" y="188" width="332" height="48" rx="8" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#cbd5e1" />
				<text x="58" y="75" fill="#1e3a8a" font-size="13">Identity Architecture</text>
				<text x="224" y="75" fill="#1f2937" font-size="13">Operational Security</text>
				<text x="58" y="146" fill="#1f2937" font-size="13">Access Governance · Zero Trust · Privacy Engineering</text>
				<text x="58" y="217" fill="#1f2937" font-size="13">Enterprise-scale Automation and Auditability</text>
			</svg>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Identity as Enterprise Infrastructure</h2>
		<p>Enterprise security is fundamentally a problem of trust architecture. Identity is the control plane. Operations is the execution layer. Privacy is an architectural constraint—not an afterthought. Automation is the scaling mechanism.</p>
		<p>
			I design systems where identity, governance, and operational security work as a unified trust infrastructure. My focus is not only enforcing access decisions, but engineering environments where those decisions are measurable, auditable, and resilient at enterprise scale.
		</p>
		<p>The goal: security that scales with organizational complexity, not against it.</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Core Expertise & Technical Pillars</h2>
		<div class="grid">
			<article class="card">
				<h3>Identity & Access Management (IAM/IGA/PAM)</h3>
				<ul>
					<li>JML and RBAC design for enterprise workflows</li>
					<li>SaaS integration: Azure AD / Entra ID, SailPoint</li>
					<li>JWT and OpenID Connect architecture patterns</li>
					<li>Privileged access controls and governance models</li>
					<li>Identity lifecycle automation and access reviews</li>
				</ul>
			</article>
			<article class="card">
				<h3>Security & Privacy Engineering</h3>
				<ul>
					<li>Zero Trust architecture principles and implementation</li>
					<li>Threat modeling and risk-informed control selection</li>
					<li>Privacy by Design and GDPR-aligned architecture</li>
					<li>Data lifecycle control and minimization strategy</li>
					<li>Enterprise security compliance frameworks</li>
				</ul>
			</article>
			<article class="card">
				<h3>Distributed Ledger & Decentralized Identity</h3>
				<ul>
					<li>Self-Sovereign Identity (SSI) architectures</li>
					<li>Verifiable Credentials (VC DM 1.1/2.0) integration</li>
					<li>EBSI and Hyperledger Besu context</li>
					<li>Credential issuance, verification, disclosure flows</li>
					<li>Trust frameworks for enterprise digital identity</li>
				</ul>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Selected Case Studies</h2>
		<article class="card">
			<h3>Decentralized Employment Verification System</h3>
			<p><strong>Challenge:</strong> Build a privacy-preserving SSI employment verification model for multi-party enterprise workflows.</p>
			<ul>
				<li>SSI platform integration with EBSI and walt.id</li>
				<li>Credential lifecycle: issuance, selective disclosure, verification</li>
				<li>Microservice boundaries for issuer, holder, and verifier domains</li>
				<li>Governance model for compliance and operational scalability</li>
			</ul>
			<p><strong>Outcome:</strong> Privacy-engineered identity infrastructure enabling trust without centralized control.</p>
		</article>
		<article class="card" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
			<h3>Corporate IAM Modernization</h3>
			<p><strong>Challenge:</strong> Redesign IAM lifecycle patterns for better access governance and reduced provisioning friction.</p>
			<ul>
				<li>RBAC model rationalization and JML alignment</li>
				<li>Automation of access provisioning workflows</li>
				<li>Integration strategy across enterprise SaaS applications</li>
				<li>Improved audit traceability and governance consistency</li>
			</ul>
			<p><strong>Outcome:</strong> Sustainable, automation-driven governance reducing operational friction while strengthening compliance.</p>
		</article>
		<article class="card" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
			<h3>Privacy Engineering & Zero Trust Integration</h3>
			<p><strong>Challenge:</strong> Introduce privacy-by-design controls in enterprise identity and data handling workflows.</p>
			<ul>
				<li>DPIA-supported privacy risk assessments</li>
				<li>Data minimization and retention control patterns</li>
				<li>ZKP and differential privacy feasibility analysis</li>
				<li>Risk-informed alignment with governance controls</li>
			</ul>
			<p><strong>Outcome:</strong> Privacy-engineered identity systems aligned with Zero Trust principles and compliance requirements.</p>
		</article>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Research & Thought Leadership</h2>
		<p>I write and think at the intersection of identity architecture, enterprise security, and trust infrastructure:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Zero Trust as enterprise infrastructure control plane</li>
			<li>Identity governance beyond compliance: automation and resilience</li>
			<li>Privacy engineering in IAM systems: practical implementation</li>
			<li>Decentralized identity in enterprise context: integration patterns</li>
			<li>Automation-driven security: reducing friction without compromising control</li>
		</ul>
		<p>Strong security begins with architectural clarity—not product selection.</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Current Focus & Capabilities</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Enterprise IAM architecture design and implementation</li>
			<li>Zero Trust strategy and deployment</li>
			<li>Access governance transformation and automation</li>
			<li>Privacy-by-design identity systems</li>
			<li>Digital identity and decentralized trust frameworks</li>
			<li>Identity-aware cloud infrastructure</li>
			<li>Automation strategies for governance and compliance</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Writing & Research</h2>
		<p>I publish essays and technical explorations on identity architecture, zero trust, and enterprise security at the intersection of operational excellence and privacy engineering. Writing appears under the <a href={`${basePath}projects/`}>projects</a> section.</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Let's Connect</h2>
		<p>Open to collaborations, advisory roles, and innovative projects in enterprise identity, cybersecurity, and zero trust architecture.</p>
		<p>LinkedIn: <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/your-linkedin" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">your-linkedin-profile</a></p>
		<p>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/yourusername" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">your-github-username</a></p>
		<p>Email: <a href="mailto:your.email@example.com">your.email@example.com</a></p>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>